[SN]TITLE[SN]
Get Inspired: Sporting Equals project taking tennis to faith centres

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Get Inspired visits a mosque in Manchester to see the Sporting Equals and Tennis Foundation Serves project, which takes tennis to faith centres.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
"I don't think I'd be playing tennis if it wasn't at the mosque," says 18-year-old Hamza.
Waled Ahmed, a project manager and coach for the project, adds: "There's definitely been an improvement in the children - with their behaviour and especially their confidence.
"They're trying out a new sport - before they'd just be playing football and nothing else.
"It gives them the confidence to pick up a racquet and start playing tennis."
